#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:5
msgid "Download VTK with Git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:8
msgid ""
"This page documents how to download VTK source code through [Git][]. See the "
"[README](README.md) for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:13
msgid "Clone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:16
msgid "Clone VTK using the commands:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:18
msgid ""
"$ git clone https://gitlab.kitware.com/vtk/vtk.git VTK\n"
"$ cd VTK\n"
"$ git submodule update --init\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:22
msgid "Update"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:25
msgid ""
"Users that have made no local changes and simply want to update a clone with "
"the latest changes may run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:28
msgid "$ git pull\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:30
msgid ""
"Avoid making local changes unless you have read our [developer instructions]"
"[]."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:34
msgid "Release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:37
msgid ""
"After cloning your local repository will be configured to follow the "
"upstream `master` branch by default.  One may create a local branch to track "
"the upstream `release` branch instead, which should guarantee only bug fixes "
"to the functionality available in the latest release:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:42
msgid "$ git checkout --track -b release origin/release\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:44
msgid ""
"This local branch will always follow the latest release. Use the [above "
"instructions](#update) to update it. Alternatively one may checkout a "
"specific release tag:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:48
msgid "$ git checkout v6.2.0\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:50
msgid ""
"Release tags never move.  Repeat the command with a different tag to get a "
"different release.  One may list available tags:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:53
msgid "$ git tag\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developers_guide/git/download.md:55
msgid "and then checkout any tag listed."
msgstr ""
